snippet.textDisplay:
TLDR: If not for yourself, be careful for other's sake. ^^,

It's a good thing that you spread awareness, you can't always tell who is in the risk group. My fiancé is a 30 y.o. woman, but she has a hereditary autoimmune disease called juvenile polyposis, she's heavily asthmatic and because of her disease she had to surgically remove her entire stomach, so she has quarantined herself. I'm not worried about getting sick myself, but I'm terrified that I could infect her so I take every precaution I can because I don't want to be a widower at 30..

Thank you so much for taking this seriously and for making other take it seriously too! <3
